    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Plywood Sub-Flooring</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If plywood sub-floor is present, check condition of plywood for damage.</para>
            <para>If damage or wear to the floor covering is under the passenger seat areas, the seats must be removed
                to repair the area affected.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the seats in the area to be repaired. Follow the procedure for seat removal as
                outlined in the Seats and Seating Removal section of this manual.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the flooring material that has been damaged or worn.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure the new flooring for fit.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the plywood sub-floor is damaged, measure the area and remove the existing plywood.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fill and seal any holes in floor from previously mounted plywood, clean adhesives from floor
                and prepare surface for replacement plywood.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
